# Shell scripts must stay LF on disk: they run under WSL/Linux bash, which chokes on
# CRLF line endings ("set: -: invalid option", syntax error). This overrides the global
# core.autocrlf=true, which was rewriting run_vllm_server.sh to CRLF on Windows-side
# checkouts and breaking the WSL CosyVoice TTS launch (and the launcher's bash call).
*.sh text eol=lf
